<%# Phase 26 — 01c. Discord webhook pane.

    Settings pane for the install-level Discord webhook. Submits to
    `PATCH /settings/discord_webhook` (mounted as
    `Settings::DiscordWebhooksController#update`). The controller:

      1. Validates the URL against `DISCORD_URL_REGEX` (accepts both
         `discord.com` and `discordapp.com` host forms).
      2. Fires a test ping via `Webhooks::DiscordClient#ping` — the
         payload uses Discord's required `content` field (not `text`).
      3. Only persists the row (`notification_delivery_channels`,
         `kind = "discord"`) when the ping returns 2xx.

    The two checkboxes (`everything`, `daily_digest`) cross the wire
    as `"yes"` / `"no"` per CLAUDE.md hard rules. The controller's
    `coerce_boolean` helper flips them back to Boolean for storage.

    The pane reads current state from the AR row (if any). When no
    row exists yet both checkboxes render unchecked and the URL
    field renders empty. %>
<%# 2026-05-11 — `totp-modal` Stimulus controller intercepts the
    submit when 2FA is on; the layout-level TOTP verification modal
    collects the code and re-submits with `totp_code` attached. The
    inline `2FA code` text input that used to render above
    `[update]` is gone — the modal IS the surface. When 2FA is off,
    `required` is "no" and the submit passes through untouched. %>
<div class="pane">
  <%= form_with url: settings_discord_webhook_path, method: :patch, local: true,
                data: {
                  controller: "totp-modal",
                  action: "submit->totp-modal#maybeIntercept",
                  totp_modal_required_value: Current.user&.totp_enabled? ? "yes" : "no"
                } do |_f| %>
    <fieldset style="padding: 8px; margin-bottom: 8px; border: none;">
      <legend><h2>Discord</h2></legend>

      <p class="text-muted">
        paste a Discord webhook URL to deliver pito notifications to a Discord channel.<br>
        the URL is verified with a test ping before it is saved.
      </p>

      <div style="margin-bottom: 6px;">
        <label for="discord_webhook_url" class="form-label">webhook URL</label>
        <input type="text" name="discord_webhook_url" id="discord_webhook_url"
               value="<%= @discord_webhook&.webhook_url %>"
               placeholder="https://discord.com/api/webhooks/.../..."
               autocomplete="off"
               style="max-width: 420px; width: 100%;">
      </div>

      <div style="margin-bottom: 6px;">
        <label class="md-check">
          <input type="checkbox" name="everything" value="yes"
                 <%= "checked" if @discord_webhook&.everything %>>
          <span class="md-check-indicator"></span>
          <span class="md-check-label">deliver every notification</span>
        </label>
      </div>

      <div style="margin-bottom: 6px;">
        <label class="md-check">
          <input type="checkbox" name="daily_digest" value="yes"
                 <%= "checked" if @discord_webhook&.daily_digest %>>
          <span class="md-check-indicator"></span>
          <span class="md-check-label">daily digest</span>
        </label>
        <span class="form-hint" style="display: block;">sent daily at 09:00 in your time zone.</span>
      </div>

      <%# Unchecked boxes post no value at all; the controller's
          `coerce_boolean` helper treats absence as `false`. This
          matches the existing Voyage pane checkbox pattern. %>

      <%# 2026-05-11 — fresh TOTP gate. When 2FA is on the layout-level
          TOTP modal opens on `[update]`; the inline 6-digit text input
          this pane used to render is gone. The controller-side
          `RecentTotpVerification` gate still reads `params[:totp_code]`
          — the modal injects it as a hidden field on the form before
          re-submitting. %>

      <div style="display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 8px;">
        <button type="submit">[update]</button>
        <%# 2026-05-11 — middle-dot separator between `[update]` and
            `[help]`, matching the `nav-sep` pattern from the channel
            show page (between the in-app `[+]` and the external
            `[youtube channel]`). %>
        <span class="nav-sep" aria-hidden="true">·</span>
        <%# Phase 26 — 01d. `[help]` link opens the layout-level
            webhook help modal with the Discord guide. The href is
            the full Markdown fragment URL so JS-off users still
            land on a usable page (the controller renders the same
            fragment without a layout, but a direct hit returns HTML
            readable in any browser). %>
        <%= render(BracketedLinkComponent.new(
              label: "help",
              href: settings_webhooks_help_path(provider: "discord"),
              data: {
                action: "click->webhook-help-modal#open",
                webhook_help_modal_provider_param: "discord"
              }
            )) %>
      </div>
    </fieldset>
  <% end %>
</div>
